+ # Secrets & Credentials
+
+ ##  Jenkins Pipeline - Using Credentials
+ you will learn how to **use credentials security in Jenkins**.
+
+ pipeline {
+     agent any
+     environment {
+         INSTITUTE_NAME = "Pathnex"
+     }
+     stages {
+         stage('Checkout')
+             steps {
+                 git url: httpsL//github.com/Pathnex/sample-java-app.git'
+             }
+         }
+         stage('Use Secret') {
+             steps {
+                 withCredentials([string(credentialssId: 'PATHNEX_API_KEY', variable:
+                 sh 'echo "Using secret &API_KEY for &INSTITUTE_NAME"'
+                 }
+               }
+           }
+       }
+   }
+
+ ## Gitlab CI -using CI/CD Variables
+ you will learn how to **use GotLab CI variables securely**.
+
+ stages:
+   - build
+
+ variables:
+   INSTITUTE_NAME: "Pathnex"
+   API_KEY: "[LACEHOLDER_SECRET"
+
+ build:
+   stage: build
+   image: alpinne:latest
+   script:
+     - echo "Using secret &API_KEY for &INSTITUTE_NAME"
